  "text": "The Fetch API types in Firefox are defined in WebIDL files and implemented in C++. Here is the mapping for each type:\n\n1. **Request**:\n   - WebIDL Definition: `dom/webidl/Request.webidl` - Defines the Request interface with properties like method, url, headers, mode, credentials, cache, redirect, and integrity. Implements the Body mixin.\n   - C++ Header: `dom/fetch/Request.h` - C++ class implementation of the Request interface\n   - C++ Implementation: `dom/fetch/Request.cpp` - Methods and functionality for the Request class\n\n2. **Response**:\n   - WebIDL Definition: `dom/webidl/Response.webidl` - Defines the Response interface with status, statusText, headers, and various static methods (error, redirect, json). Includes Body mixin.\n   - C++ Header: `dom/fetch/Response.h` - C++ class implementation of the Response interface\n   - C++ Implementation: `dom/fetch/Response.cpp` - Methods and functionality for the Response class\n\n3. **Headers**:\n   - WebIDL Definition: `dom/webidl/Headers.webidl` - Defines the Headers interface with methods for managing HTTP headers (append, delete, get, set) and support for iterating over headers.\n   - C++ Header: `dom/fetch/Headers.h` - C++ class implementation of the Headers interface\n   - C++ Implementation: `dom/fetch/Headers.cpp` - Methods and functionality for the Headers class\n\n4. **FetchEvent**:\n   - WebIDL Definition: `dom/webidl/FetchEvent.webidl` - Defines the FetchEvent interface that extends ExtendableEvent, with properties for request, clientId, resultingClientId, and methods like respondWith().\n   - C++ Header: `dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.h` - C++ class implementation of FetchEvent as part of ServiceWorker event handling\n   - C++ Implementation: `dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.cpp` - Methods and functionality for the FetchEvent class\n\nThe Request, Response, and Headers implementations are located in the `dom/fetch/` directory as they are core Fetch API types. The FetchEvent implementation is in `dom/serviceworkers/` because it is specific to Service Worker event handling."
}

